#compdef emergency-login
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream jdebp/nosh
# source/emergency-login.cpp + builtins-emergency-login.cpp -
# emergency-login is a stripped-down statically-linked variant of
# system-control with only 3 builtin subcommands: builtins,
# emergency_login, and system_version (extracted from
# builtins-emergency-login.cpp `extern void <name> ( ... )`
# forward declarations).
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
# jdebp/nosh emergency-login R132d — single-binary harvest of
# the nosh emergency login shell. Statically linked so it can run
# even when the system's dynamic libraries are broken; spawned by
# system-manager as a last-resort recovery shell when the boot
# fails badly enough that normal getty + login fail.

_arguments -s -S \
  '1:subcommand:(builtins emergency-login version)' \
  '*:: :_default'
